HEADWORD: Panomphean
<hw>Pan`om*phe"an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>panomphaeus</ets>, Gr. <?/.]</ety> <def>Uttering ominous or
prophetic voices; divining.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We want no half gods, <qex>panomphean</qex> Joves.</q>
<rj><qau>Mrs. Browning.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Panoplied</ent>⟦br⟧
